The Youth Employment and Empowerment Project aims to enhance Government and UN interventions in reducing unemployment among youth in Sierra Leone and in consolidating the peace building efforts. 
Its specific objectives are: 
- to provide rapid employment opportunities and income generating activities for young people;
- to strengthen the capacity of the Youth division of the Ministry of Education, Youth and Sports;
- to promote and facilitate the participation of young people in decision making processes and the development of youth interest initiatives.

